cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper deals with computer vision and robotics problems related to urban localization. The proposed method involves semantic segmentation and registration of facades, which are typical tasks in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also introduces a Bayesian model, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves optimization and statistical modeling, which are also common in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with geometric structures, which are relevant to computer graphics (cs.GR).
